RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNIFIED FRONT pulled the rider to the lead inside at the half, lengthened stride opening up of rivals running on the turn, was urged mildly in mid stretch keeping to the task and held safe comfortably crossing the line. SMILES FOR DAVID broke sharp to have the early lead, was relegated to the chaser at the half, continued to chase in vain on the frontrunner who was extending the advantage through the turn but determinedly fought on down the stretch never giving in to be a clear second at the wire. SNOW LAKE stalked near the rear down the backstretch, was on hold behind runners with three eighths remaining, shifted to the three path two furlongs from home starting a run, shifted inwards to the fence at the top of the lane and finished up closing on the rail to get third money in the end. ALMONTE PRINCESS was unhurried to trail in he beginning, put in an early move splitting rivals at the half, continued to gain between foes at the quarter marker but could not sustain the run and stalled in the final furlong. TAYLORMOON travelled four deep tracking the top pair, was nudged for more making little gain in the three path through the turn, angled outside five wide for the drive and could not get into contention running to the finish line. SWEEPING PASSION settled in midfield between foes down the back straight, was scrubbed on the fence trying to keep up with others on the turn and backed away on the fence at the quarter pole. GAMBLER'S POSE watched the top duo in the three path down the backside, offered a brief rally three wide at the three furlong marker and had little turning for home backing away in upper stretch.

BARTICA travelled close to the back of the pack two wide in the beginning, began to pick up runners four wide on the far turn , shifted outside widest gaining momentum in the six path for the drive to the line and was one paced in the stretch but was passing weary foes to collect a minor share in the end. SEATTLE DOWN UNDER trailed the field into the first turn, continued seeing the pack three deep down the backstretch, circled around runners with a good move three wide with three eighths to go to be in range in the four path at the top of the lane but could not find more late and stalled in the final furlong. ARNIE P settled in midfield in the early stages on the race, could not keep up with others running between rivals on the far turn and made little impression in the stretch run. CHICAGO TYPHOON broke out at the start, pressed the issue outside in the first turn, chased the frontrunner down the backside, was urged for more between horses but was giving way at the quarter pole and had little to show in the stretch drive. TREBUCHET was off a bit slow breaking outwards to begin, settled in midpack on the rail into the first turn, made a brief run into the far turn, was roused to keep up with rallying foes outside with five sixteenths remaining, offered little response and faded in mid stretch.

SILENT RISK settled five deep near the rear in the early part of the backstretch running, stalked in the third flight three or four wide on the turn outside rivals, was pushed out widest turning for home in the six path and could not offer a finish outside running to the wire.
